
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to perform an HTTP POST request to a specified URL with automatic response conversion. The [http.post] slot sends a request to "https://logistics.example.org/get-user", with [convert] set to true to automatically convert the response to a suitable format. The [payload] node is included to specify the data to be sent in the request body.
http.post:"https://logistics.example.org/get-user"
   convert:true
   payload
